headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 31 points and 12 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers extended their winning streak to six games with a 119-100 win over the short-handed San Antonio Spurs on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 31, leads streaking 76ers past Spurs 119-100

headlines.description: — Back at the site of an overtime thriller in the playoffs, the Milwaukee Bucks quickly made clear this one wasn't going down to the wire.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis returns, Bucks blow out Nets 121-109 in Brooklyn

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet had 37 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists for his first career triple-double, OG Anunoby scored 22 points, and the Toronto Raptors overcame a 17-point deficit to beat the short-handed Jazz 122-108 on Friday night, snapping Utah’s...
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet's 1st career triple-double pushes Raptors over Jazz

headlines.description: — Coach Billy Donovan chose to focus more on where the Chicago Bulls need to improve than a win streak that's their longest in more than a decade.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine leads way as Bulls win 9th straight, beat Wizards

headlines.description: — Tim Hardaway Jr. had 19 points and seven assists to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 130-106 win over the Houston Rockets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hardaway leads Mavericks to 130-106 win over Rockets

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — D'Angelo Russell had 27 points and 12 assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves routed the Oklahoma City Thunder 135-105 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell, Edwards help Timberwolves rout Thunder 135-105

headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets have struggled to hold leads in the third quarter this season. When another one was slipping away, the reigning MVP carried them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores 33 points, Nuggets beat Kings, 121-111

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 23 of his 32 points in the second half, Malik Monk added a season-high 29 and the Los Angeles Lakers held off the Atlanta Hawks 134-118 Friday night for their first four-game winning streak of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron leads Lakers past Hawks 134-118 for 4th straight win

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Rajon Rondo settled right in with his newest team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland's 26 points leads Cavs in 114-101 win at Portland
